node.text:
“With the Noah Davis Prize, we are given the opportunity to shine light on somebody else, to be a lighthouse, and to hopefully lead the way for change in the art world,” says Karon Davis, artist and co-founder with her late husband, the artist Noah Davis, of the Underground Museum in Los Angeles.  The unique art space, incubator, and community hub is among the first partners of the CHANEL Culture Fund, a new global programme championing innovators across the arts. In partnership with the CHANEL Culture Fund, the first Noah Davis Prize will be awarded by the Underground Museum to three curators transforming their respective fields and broadening the audiences for culture.
 
Discover the four other CHANEL Culture Fund partners soon on IGTV.
 
#CHANELCultureFund #CHANEL #UndergroundMuseum

node.title: The Underground Museum, Los Angeles: CHANEL Culture Fund Partner

Filmmaker Loïc Prigent steps behind-the-scenes of the CHANEL ‘Le Château des Dames’ Métiers d’art 2020/21 collection in the Maisons d’art ateliers. He unveils the savoir-faire behind the collection imagined by Virginie Viard with the support of CHANEL's Métiers d'art, including Lesage, Montex, Lemarié, Lognon, Goossens, Maison Michel and Massaro.

The collection is now available in boutiques.

See more at chanel.com

“With the Noah Davis Prize, we are given the opportunity to shine light on somebody else, to be a lighthouse, and to hopefully lead the way for change in the art world,” says Karon Davis, artist and co-founder with her late husband, the artist Noah Davis, of the Underground Museum in Los Angeles.  The unique art space, incubator, and community hub is among the first partners of the CHANEL Culture Fund, a new global programme championing innovators across the arts. In partnership with the CHANEL Culture Fund, the first Noah Davis Prize will be awarded by the Underground Museum to three curators transforming their respective fields and broadening the audiences for culture.
 
Discover the four other CHANEL Culture Fund partners soon on IGTV.
 
#CHANELCultureFund #CHANEL #UndergroundMuseum

CHANEL in Cannes — actress, singer and House ambassador Vanessa Paradis attended the premiere of ‘Cette musique ne joue pour personne’ by Samuel Benchetrit as one of the main actresses. On this occasion, Vanessa Paradis wore a custom dress from the CHANEL Spring-Summer 2021 Ready-to-Wear collection.

The actress also wore CHANEL High Jewelry pieces and CHANEL make-up.
